##############00
## NAVIGATING ##
################

This file is meant to be navigated via a text editor. Each section has
a 2 digit id in hexadecimal base (255 possible ids), it is easy and
fast to jump in-between sections by using the basic string matching
functionality (ex. by matching the string '06' one should jump to the
'MISCELLANEOUS' section).




############01
## BUILDING ##
##############




    ##############02
    ## STANDALONE ##
    ################




        ##########03
        ## COORDS ##
        ############

        BUILDING:
        'make coords'

        INPUT:
        A string formatted 64-bit integer different from zero.

        OUTPUT:
        Generates a plain text file 'coords.txt' with respective
        columns 'n' progressive (coordinate-)index, 'i' row number,
        'j' column number, 'x' and 'y' standard cartesian coordinates.



        
        ################04
        ## CONNECTIVITY ##
        ##################

        BUILDING:
        'make connectivity'

        INPUT:
        A string formatted posix path to the output of the 'coords'
        program (by default 'coords.txt').

        OUTPUT:
        Generates a plain text file 'connectivity.txt' with respective
        columns 'e' progressive (edge-)index, 'n1' initial progressive
        coordinate-index and 'n2' final progressive coordinate-index.




        ############05
        ## ORDERING ##
        ##############

        BUILDING:
        'make ordering'

        INPUT:
        A string formatted posix path to the output of the 'coords'
        program (by default 'connectivity.txt').
        
        OUTPUT:
        Generates a plain text file 'ordering.txt' with respective
        columns 'm' new progressive coordinate-index and 'n' original
        progressive coordinate-index.



    
    #################06
    ## MISCELLANEOUS ##
    ###################

    1) Cleaning after a succesful build can be done with 'make clean'.
    2) Debug builds can be accessed by pre-pending 'debug-' to any of
       the listed build commands:
       (ex. 'make coords' -> 'make debug-coords')